rawContent:
The most relevant point in a bull run is to:

BLOCK OUT EMOTIONS.

The current phase is already giving us the opportunity to practise this.

You see your portfolio rising - fine.

Your portfolio makes ATH after ATH - fine.

Try not to fall into euphoria.

Take a neutral view & continue to focus on YOUR plan.

Don't pay attention to the numbers.

Pay attention to what you have planned.

Don't look at your portfolio every hour.

Why would that help, you ask?

Emotions are like a wild animal that you can train and control.

The more you work on them, the better you can control them.

So what could be better than practising now?

And in a similar situation.
